From f2202ec251c3daa15066109312381bd6eacea8b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 05:23:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P2: shared-memory ring transport ABI + trust-boundary
 validator

First increment of the perf#18 (dar-dar6x4-perf-5dq.30) shared-memory ring
transport: the wire-format ABI and the pure trust-boundary validator that
gates a guest-proposed ring control block, with an adversarial RED->GREEN
unit test.

The hot-path RPC round-trip is ~90% empty cross-process wakeup latency, not
server work (measured: server services each startup call in 4-16us but the
guest waits ~100-120us). This adds the contract for moving small, reply-bearing,
fd-free C2S calls onto a shared-memory SPSC ring + futex wake, keeping UDS for
connect/auth/fd-passing/fallback. Full design: PERF18-SHMEM-RING-ABI.md.

This commit is design + the security gate only -- no call is migrated yet and
no transport is wired. The whole ABI block is gated behind DSERVER_RING_TRANSPORT
(default OFF), so a normal build is byte-identical (verified: header compiles
clean as C11 and C++17 with the flag on and off; the block has zero footprint
when off).

THE GUEST IS UNTRUSTED. dserver_ring_shm_validate() is the gate the server runs
on a COPY of the guest's control block before mapping/using the ring. It does
uint64 arithmetic only and dereferences nothing, so it is safe on fully
attacker-controlled input. It rejects: bad magic/ABI, slot_size out of range or
below the slot header, slot_count not a power of two or over the cap, total_size
!= the fd's real size or over the 16MiB cap, a ring/arena whose span escapes the
mapping or overlaps another region or the header, and a guest_tid that doesn't
match the SCM-credentialed nsid.

RED->GREEN (standing TDD rule): tests/ring_shm_validate_test.cpp is proven RED
against an accept-all stub validator (-DRING_VALIDATE_STUB -> all 15 adversarial
cases fail) and GREEN against the real validator. tests/run-ring-shm-validate.sh
runs both arms and exits 0 only if RED fails and GREEN passes.

Not pushed. Prod darlingserver a13ec2ae untouched (this is source-only on a fix
branch; nothing built or deployed).
