From c0440aa39d375a5ec55a44b98010b82042e97dc2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 06:28:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P3: ring datapath (SPSC + C2S service + reply) +
 guest task_self_trap

Server side of the shared-memory ring fast path, end-to-end and host-proven:

- rpc-supplement.h: pure, bounds-safe SPSC datapath (free-running head/tail,
  single release-store publish, corrupt-distance -> empty/full), the ring
  message convention (reply hdr {code} + body), and dserver_ring_service_c2s()
  -- the server's request-drain/reply-publish loop. All offsets-only, derefs no
  guest pointer, clamps every length to the slot. Wake design Variant 2: the
  reply gains a wake_fd @fd the server hands the guest (the only thing its epoll
  loop can wait on); the reverse wake is FUTEX_WAKE on s2c_futex.

- generate-rpc-wrappers.py: ring_attach reply gains wake_fd @fd.

- ring.cpp/.hpp: RingBuffer::publishReply (claim s2c slot, write code+body,
  one release-store publish), wakeGuest (bump s2c_futex + FUTEX_WAKE non-private),
  drainWake.

- call.cpp: darRingServiceC2S() rebuilds each request as the SAME UDS-format
  Message, arms a one-shot ring-reply sink (Thread::beginRingReply), and runs it
  inline via the perf#2b doWork() path -- reusing the entire Call dispatch (so
  dar-l8k / dar-6x4 / dar-gwn fixes all still apply); only transport in + reply
  sink out differ. P3 allowlist = task_self_trap. Monitor cb drains the wake
  eventfd then services c2s.

- thread.cpp: pushCallReply redirects a ring-originated reply onto the s2c ring
  + wakes the guest (falls back to UDS if s2c is full); beginRingReply state.

RED->GREEN host gate tests/ring_datapath_test.cpp on a real memfd ring: happy
round-trip, FIFO batch, and adversarial containment (length>slot, corrupt tail,
backpressure retry-not-loss, refused callnum) under ASan. RED arm = accept-all
stub, must fail. run-ring-shm-validate.sh now runs validator(15)+attach(8)+
datapath(GREEN+RED).

VERIFIED: full darlingserver builds+links flag-OFF (default) AND flag-ON; gates
green. All gated behind DSERVER_RING_TRANSPORT (default OFF). Nothing deployed.
