From 7ade3234c1d3746cd3c4a47a1014758b0ecc8f0f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 09:23:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P6.1 step 2 (dar-ohp): surgical direct ring dispatch
 for mach_reply_port

Step 1 ran the allowlisted no-block ops without the microthread fiber but still
paid the generic RPC framing per call: rebuild a UDS Message, re-look-up the
thread in the registry via callFromMessage, heap-allocate a Call, decode. The P6
breakdown flagged that framing (~579ns dispatch + alloc) as the next removable
cost for the single hottest trap.

This adds Thread::doMachReplyPortInline(seq): for EXACTLY mach_reply_port (empty
body, no arena) the ring service loop skips ALL of it. The thread is already held
as a shared_ptr for the whole slot iteration, so its lifetime is guaranteed
without the registry lookup; the inline op establishes the SAME duct-tape context
as doWorkInline (currentThreadVar + dtape_thread_entering, so current_task()
resolves identically), calls the bare dtape_mach_reply_port() primitive -- the
identical trap MachReplyPort::processCall uses, NOT a reimplementation -- and
publishes the {replyhdr.code=0}{uint32 port_name} reply straight onto the s2c
ring (byte-identical to the generic reply). NO Call, NO Message, NO callFromMessage.

Surgical, one op only -- NOT a general dispatcher. Anything else (callnum mismatch,
any payload/arena, or the inline op declining because the thread is busy/dead)
falls back to the generic step-1 callFromMessage + doWorkInline path, which
validates fully. Shape guard (reqlen==0 && arena_len==0) is the security boundary
for the no-Call path. Escape hatches unchanged: DARLING_SERVER_FAST_OPS=0 (global)
/ DARLING_SERVER_FAST_MACH_REPLY_PORT=0 (per-op) route the op back through the
framed path; with the global hatch off, ring_fast_hit stays 0.

Counters ring_fast_hit / ring_fast_fallback in the stat JSON.

Live A/B (ring ON, 5x20000 isolated mach_reply_port round-trips, null=0 both arms):
  fast ON  (default): ~943-967 ns/call median, ring_fast_hit=101594 fast_fallback=0
  fast OFF (FAST_OPS=0): ~4480-4800 ns/call, ring_fast_hit=0 (generic path)
~4.7x over the generic ring path, ~0.95us median (target was <3us). 60k+ clean
mint+free with null=0 in both arms = identical port semantics. Fork-storm
correctness 3/3 DONE (.o=200/200, clients_blocked=0) -- no dar-l8k/dar-6x4 regress.

RED->GREEN gate: tests/ring_fastpath_gate_test.c gains the fastMachReplyPortEligible
shape predicate; -DNO_SHAPE_GUARD RED arm (drops the shape check) must fail the
payload/arena-rejection assertions. Wired into run-ring-shm-validate.sh. All ring
gates GREEN; both RED arms (-DFASTPATH_NO_HATCH, -DNO_SHAPE_GUARD) correctly fail.

Server-only; default OFF (gated DSERVER_RING_TRANSPORT). Prod restored OFF.
