From d010da11228e6fbde4e3db2ba8b2182310db6bc7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 10:14:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P7 (dar-my8): wake-model lost-wake race gate + full
 per-op counters

The v3 wake model's whole win is two conditional decisions (guest doorbell only
when server not ACTIVE_POLLING; server FUTEX_WAKE only when a guest is parked).
Now that the hot path is ~740ns p50, a missed doorbell/wake that strands a
request or reply forever is the costliest possible bug (gist 191a10db / 33355bf).
This adds a deterministic RED->GREEN gate on the two lost-wake invariants.

tests/ring_wake_race_test.cpp -- two parts:
 (a) EXHAUSTIVE ordering enumeration (the authoritative gate): models each side's
     race-window micro-ops over a real shared control block using the REAL
     predicates, and enumerates EVERY interleaving of the two sequences, asserting
     ZERO lose the wake.
       REQUEST side: guest publish + conditional doorbell vs server
         ACTIVE_POLLING -> SLEEP_ARMED -> critical recheck -> SLEEPING_EPOLL.
         Invariant: the request is always serviced (recheck drains it, or the
         guest doorbelled because server_state != ACTIVE_POLLING).
       RESPONSE side: server publishReply + conditional FUTEX_WAKE vs guest
         set-waiter-bit -> recheck -> FUTEX_WAIT. Invariant: a guest that commits
         to sleeping is always woken (sees the reply in its post-set recheck, or
         the server saw the waiter bit and woke it).
     Exact, instant, deterministic. RED arms break each safety mechanism:
       -DRACE_NO_SERVER_RECHECK -> request side finds 5 lost interleavings (FAILS).
       -DRACE_WAITERBIT_AFTER_RECHECK -> response side finds 1 (FAILS).
 (b) concurrent two-thread stress (pinned to distinct cores) on a real shm ring --
     corroborates (a) on real silicon. DIAGNOSTIC ONLY (reports watchdog timeouts,
     never fails the gate): its round handshake + modeled park are scheduling-
     sensitive, and a flaky stress gate is the CI hazard the gist warns against.
     The RED->GREEN contract rests entirely on the exact enumeration.

Verified: GREEN exits 0 even under 12 CPU hogs (stress timeout is diagnostic);
both RED arms exit 1 on the enumeration. Wired into run-ring-shm-validate.sh.

Per-op counters (gist required hit/fallback/fail/s2c_full/suspend): adds
ring_fast_fail, ring_s2c_full, ring_fast_suspend to the stat JSON alongside the
existing ring_fast_hit/ring_fast_fallback. Incremented at the real sites --
publishReply returning full (s2c_full) in doMachReplyPortInline + pushCallReply;
the inline suspend detection in doWorkInline + doMachReplyPortInline (must stay 0;
nonzero = an allowlist misclassification); ring fast-path fallback dispatch
throwing (fast_fail).

Server-only; default OFF (gated DSERVER_RING_TRANSPORT). Nothing deployed/pushed.
