Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 (dar-1il.3 / .3.1): duplex-lane design + the
 wake-model hard gate (RED->GREEN)

P8 = minimal duplex ring prototype for the one known bad case (mach_port_deallocate of a
mapped-region-backed port: the destroy drives a vm-munmap S2C upcall to a caller parked on the
simple ring -> deadlock; this sank deallocate dar-1il.1 + mod_refs dar-1il.2). The duplex lane
lets a parked caller service that S2C while awaiting its own reply.

This commit lands the LOAD-BEARING first step: the duplex wake-model DESIGN + its exhaustive
RED->GREEN gate, BEFORE any transport wiring (mirrors dar-my8's discipline for the simple ring).
Pure logic, hermetic, instant -- the duplex lane is rejected unless this is GREEN.

tests/PERF18-DUPLEX-LANE-DESIGN.md (new): the problem from the real code (_s2cPerform sends the
S2C over UDS + blocks on _s2cReplySempahore; a ring-parked gr_wait_reply guest can't service it);
the Lane-2 minimal protocol (4 message classes, one parent in flight/thread, one outstanding
upcall, caller-thread pump, UDS fallback on unexpected shape); the wake model's TWO waiter
relationships on one parked thread; RED arms; the P8 acceptance ladder.

tests/ring_duplex_wake_gate_test.c (new) + run-ring-shm-validate.sh: the gate. GREEN proves
  - DUPLEX-GUEST: a guest parked for its final reply never sleeps through a published S2C upcall
    (exhaustive interleaving enumeration over the real publish-before-read-bit predicate; 0 lost);
  - DUPLEX-PUMP: the pump drains ALL upcalls in a burst (while, not if) -- none stranded;
  - DUPLEX-SERVER: the server parked for the C2S upcall reply never sleeps through it (0 lost);
  - correlation: a reply is accepted ONLY on matching upcall_id / parent_id.
RED arms each break one mechanism and the binary exits nonzero:
  -DDUPLEX_NO_GUEST_PUMP (one-shot drain strands a burst upcall),
  -DDUPLEX_WAITERBIT_AFTER_RECHECK (bit set after recheck -> lost wake both sides),
  -DDUPLEX_WRONG_CORRELATION (accepts a mismatched id -> resume on the wrong reply).

Full perf#18 ring gate suite GREEN incl. the new ring_duplex_wake gate; simple Lane-1 fast ring
UNTOUCHED. Next (Phase D proper): wire the duplex transport, migrate deallocate of a
mapped-region-backed port, side-effect A/B vs UDS under a real boot, simple-ring perf unchanged.
NOTHING PUSHED.
