From 4965126580440a8f75bb179111b4a7b58c4dd3d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 03:22:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D3 (dar-1il.3.1.1): server duplex
 _s2cTryDuplexLocked + drain + sentinel

Server side of the end-to-end duplex selftest. A synthetic S2C ECHO upcall now
travels server -> ring-parked guest -> reply through the REAL transport + real
server code -- the last bridge before mach_port_deallocate can migrate (Phase E,
still blocked on this). NO real op rides the duplex lane yet.

thread.cpp:
 - _s2cTryDuplexLocked(): the iron 7-condition conjunction guard (v4 ring + SELFTEST
   cap + supported shape + one-outstanding + clean mailbox + nonzero correlation ids +
   same-ring) then publishes the S2C upcall into the duplex mailbox + wakes the guest.
   This is the SHARED guarded-publish primitive a real op will use in Phase E.
 - _drainDuplexReply(): main-loop harvest of the correlated reply. Completion is a
   STATE MACHINE (publish upcall + return; a later drain sees the reply + publishes the
   parent final reply), NOT a fiber park -- so the server wait is intrinsically scoped
   to the op and the main loop keeps draining other clients. Mis-correlated reply ->
   reject + fail the parent (ringDuplexReject). Lock-free _duplexInFlightFast atomic so
   the hot Lane-1 drain pays one relaxed load/thread (no rwlock) when nothing is in flight.
 - duplexSelftestUpcall(): the sentinel kickoff (publish + return).

call.cpp: recognize the sentinel parent op DSERVER_RING_DUPLEX_SELFTEST_CALLNUM in
   ringServiceThread BEFORE the eligible check, env-gated DARLING_SERVER_DUPLEX_SELFTEST=1
   (server env only). Guard-decline -> immediate failure reply (never a fabricated success).

server.cpp: call drainDuplexReply() per ring thread in _drainRings (the resume point).
ring.cpp/.hpp: liveControlBlock() + duplexCapable() reach the shared-page duplex mailbox.
metrics: ring_duplex_s2c / ring_duplex_reject counters.

