From 84c16d0833a9573f61df677be083526f15d81c56 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 07:45:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D6 (dar-1il.3.2.x): caller-S2C duplex SIDEBAND +
 live cure proof (server)

Reframe the duplex lane from "the route for guest vm_deallocate" (which no guest
ever sends -- self vm_deallocate resolves to the mach_task_self() fast-path name
and runs locally, never reaching the server) to a general CALLER-S2C SIDEBAND for
any ring-parked parent op whose server-side processing drives an internal munmap
S2C back to the caller. This cures the real reachable deadlock class, not a
specific trap.

