From 897b0e1e8f82b3b2b0ab9e2c2dbba640c3868d40 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 11:07:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D11 (dar-1il.6): migrate uidgid +
 set_thread_handles + started_suspended + get_tracer + task_is_64_bit as
 Tier-1 generic-fiber ring ops (server)

The D9-heatmap-surfaced bulk closed-fast Lane-1 batch, the follow-on after D10 closed
the pure-mint self-trap family. These 5 ops are CLOSED request->single-reply
transactions with a FIXED inline request body and a FIXED inline reply body (or
header-only), no fd-passing, no caller-S2C, no destroy -- they pass all 5 membership
canon rules. Unlike the self-trap family they ride the GENERIC fiber doWork() path
(Tier-1), NOT the no-fiber inline path: they read/mutate process/thread state via the
generic Call pipeline, not pure mint.

Server side is purely additive: adding them to DSERVER_RING_C2S_OPCODES (the single
shared allowlist + opcode-hash) makes the existing generic eligible-op path service
them -- it rebuilds {callhdr, body}, dispatches via callFromMessage -> doWork (the same
dtape primitive as UDS), and the reply BODY rides the ring verbatim via
_publishReplyToRingLocked (everything after the reply hdr). No per-op server code.
DSERVER_RING_OP_CLASS tags each SIMPLE_C2S only (NOT NOFIBER_FAST); the canon-safe
static_assert still holds. ABI stays v5 (opcode-hash handles the set change; a skewed
guest is rejected at attach -> all-UDS, never a silent drop).

Gates: ring_lane_class_gate_test.c + ring_allowlist_test.cpp updated with explicit GREEN
assertions for all 5 (SIMPLE_C2S, NOT NOFIBER_FAST, NOT destroy/S2C); full perf#18 ring
suite RED->GREEN OK incl. drift + the C++ canon static_assert.

Live A/B (homebrew-test prefix, heatmap armed): uidgid, set_thread_handles, task_is_64_bit
all moved 100% UDS -> mostly-ring (verdict already-on-ring, used_fiber=total confirming
Tier-1, caller_s2c=0); started_suspended/get_tracer stay UDS (they run only in the dyld
VARIANT early bootstrap before ring attach -- expected pre-attach residual). Ring health
clean (fast_fail/fast_fallback/s2c_full/fast_suspend=0). Side-effect A/B byte-identical
ring-vs-UDS (id/uidgid/sysctl-64bit/ps outputs). Skew (D11 server + old UDS dylib) clean,
no wedge. Fork-storm 3/3 (30 children each, fail=0).

Guest side is in the matching xnu commit.
