+	// perf #18 D11 (dar-1il.6): the bulk closed-fast Lane-1 batch. Each must be SimpleRingC2SEligible
+	// (Lane 1), Tier-1 ONLY (NOT NoFiberFast -- they read/mutate process/thread state via the generic
+	// Call path, not pure mint), and carry NEITHER destroy nor caller-S2C (so the canon-safe fold holds).
+#define D11_OP_CHECK(op) do { \
+		uint32_t _c = dserver_ring_op_class((uint32_t)dserver_callnum_##op); \
+		CHECK((_c & DSERVER_RING_CLASS_SIMPLE_C2S) != 0u, #op " is SimpleRingC2SEligible [D11]"); \
+		CHECK((_c & DSERVER_RING_CLASS_NOFIBER_FAST) == 0u, #op " is NOT NoFiberFastEligible (Tier 1 only) [D11]"); \
+		CHECK((_c & (DSERVER_RING_CLASS_DESTROY | DSERVER_RING_CLASS_CALLER_S2C)) == 0u, #op " is NEITHER destroy nor caller-S2C [D11]"); \
+	} while (0);
+	D11_OP_CHECK(uidgid);
+	D11_OP_CHECK(set_thread_handles);
+	D11_OP_CHECK(started_suspended);
+	D11_OP_CHECK(get_tracer);
+	D11_OP_CHECK(task_is_64_bit);
+#undef D11_OP_CHECK
+
 	// --- the UDS-only ops are tagged destroy-capable + caller-S2C, and are NOT SimpleRingC2SEligible
 	//     (the canon's whole point: "wrong lane, not bad op") ------------------------------------
 	uint32_t dealloc = dserver_ring_op_class(dserver_callnum_mach_port_deallocate);

From 070954ea8ae50b7e782dc7c6276f2068ba68a789 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 11:30:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf#18=20D12=20(dar-1il.7):=20ack-only=20sette?=
 =?UTF-8?q?r=20ring-migration=20recon=20=E2=80=94=20STOP=20verdict?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Recon-only, no code migrated. Surveyed all closed setter-shape ops for the
ACK-ONLY Lane-1 migration (caller still waits for a status reply; NOT true async,
no arena, no psynch, no duplex). Verdict: no clean WARM ack-only batch exists.

- Warm clean-shape op (interrupt_exit) DISQUALIFIED: re-sends savedReply over UDS,
  coupled to the per-thread interrupt reply-matching protocol.
- Warm not-yet-migrated setters are pre-attach (set_dyld_info, set_executable_path
  in mldr, before ring attach) and/or arena-class (char* path) and/or NO_REPLY.
- Clean ack-only-fixed ops (set_tracer, ptrace_sigexc, ptrace_thupdate,
  stop_after_exec) are all already-synchronous + canon-safe but COLD (ptrace /
  start-suspended only) -> ~0 reclaimable in build/run workloads.

The fixed-shape ack-only setter seam is exhausted for warm traffic after D10+D11.
Next perf lever recommendation (NOT a D12 deliverable): the variable-length ARENA
lane (vchroot_path 248 + mldr_path 82 + set_executable_path 83, all char*).

