From bacdb644260835df43f5dfa9b9bf2c1c0cecb90b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 13:04:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#23 (dar-dar6x4-perf-5dq.23): M1 spike gate for
 server-side posix_spawn pidns placement

Standalone HOST RED/GREEN gate pinning the namespace primitive the M1 spawn-helper
depends on: a process forked from OUTSIDE the guest PID ns (like a darlingserver
worker fork) is NOT in the guest ns (RED, the reason the current server can't place a
spawn into the guest), while a process forked by a MEMBER of the guest ns (the
spike-helper, child of the PID-1 clone) IS in it (GREEN). Uses clone(CLONE_NEWPID);
re-execs under unshare --user --pid when unprivileged. No booted guest needed.

Committing previously-untracked working-tree files so this perf#23 spike work is not
lost. Not wired into CMake / no test-runner reference yet -- run manually:
  bash tests/run-spawn-helper-pidns-placement.sh
(Belongs to perf#23, not the perf#18 ring epic; preserved here on the shared branch.)
---
 tests/run-spawn-helper-pidns-placement.sh |  59 +++++++
 tests/spawn_helper_pidns_placement.c      | 203 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 262 insertions(+)
