From ae0238fa652688bfda98965cf3ce6e124d2437cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 13:39:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 D15a (dar-dar6x4-perf-5dq / dar-1il.10): ring-attach
 timeline/reclaimability census -> REFUTES "move attach earlier"; real lever =
 per-thread ring ownership

RECON-ONLY. Default-OFF instrumentation only (env DARLING_SERVER_ATTACH_CENSUS=1). No attach move,
no op migration, no arena/duplex/psynch. Lane-1 set unchanged (13 ops).

INSTRUMENTATION (all default-OFF; hot path byte-identical when disarmed):
- Metrics D15a block (metrics.hpp): attachCensusOn + per-callnum preAttachUdsByCallnum /
  postAttachUdsByCallnum / preAttachEligibleUdsByCallnum + aggregate timeline counters +
  attachOrdinalHistogram + attach attempt/reject tallies + attachRejectByReason[]. Recording
  methods recordAttachCensusUdsCall / recordAttachOutcome / recordAttachBinaryFact.
- Process (process.hpp): _udsCallOrdinal (per-process UDS-call counter) + _ringAttachedAtOrdinal
  (first-writer-wins latch) + cheap atomic accessors.
- Call::ringEligibleCallnum (call.cpp): static classifier mirroring DSERVER_RING_C2S_OPCODES.
- Sites: server.cpp:723 (the GENUINE UDS receive choke point -- ring calls dispatch in
  ringServiceThread and never pass here) + RingAttach::processCall (attach outcome + ordinal latch).
- Snapshot: metrics.cpp attach_census* block (zeros/empty unless armed).
- Gate: tests/attach_census_gate_test.cpp (GREEN + 2 RED arms: disarmed-noop, eligible-split);
  wired into run-ring-shm-validate.sh. Full perf#18 suite GREEN.

FINDING (same warm workload, 500 processes, 10368 RPC): the D14 INFERENCE that the reclaimable UDS
tail is pre-attach is REFUTED by direct measurement. attach_census_total_pre_attach_eligible = 9 --
across all 500 processes only 9 ring-eligible UDS calls EVER occurred before the ring attached.
Attach is already very early: attach_ordinal p50=4 (a process makes ~4 UDS calls -- checkin +
ring_attach, NEITHER eligible -- then attaches). The eligible ops D14 saw on UDS are POST-attach
(2053 calls): they ride UDS AFTER the ring exists because the ring is SINGLE-OWNER (P3/P4 -- only
the attaching thread owns it; other threads fall back to UDS). Secondary: 204/704 attach attempts
(29%) rejected reason=ABI -- a homebrew-test prefix dylib-version-skew artifact (the ABI reject is
the safety valve degrading to all-UDS, ~0 in a matched prod deploy).

DECISION (among A handshake-attach / B early mldr-init / C attach-on-first-eligible / D prewarm):
STOP -- all four target the pre-attach window, which holds 9 reclaimable calls. C is already the
status quo and already fires by ordinal ~4. The reclaimable UDS is the 2053 POST-attach eligible
calls, root-caused to the single-owner ring, NOT attach timing. Real next lever (DIFFERENT bead,
NOT D15a scope) = dar-1il.11 (D16): PER-THREAD ring ownership (the P4 "full per-thread rings" P3
deferred), so a non-owner thread's eligible ops ride the ring instead of UDS.

LESSON: "op observed on UDS" != "op ran before attach." Measure the window before re-architecting
to widen it. Doc tests/PERF18-ATTACH-TIMELINE-D15a.md + -snapshot.json. Prod binaries restored.
Nothing pushed.
