From aa5b5dc29279ebf39fd81914cad51e1e808ddac3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 14:54:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 D17 (dar-dar6x4-perf-5dq / dar-1il.12): post-D16
 residual-UDS classifier + heatmap (recon)

RECON-only, default-OFF (DARLING_SERVER_RESIDUAL_CENSUS=1). After per-thread lanes (D16) the
eligible-UDS pool dropped 1533->231; D17 classifies that residual to decide if it is (A)
unavoidable first-eligible-before-this-thread's-lane, (B) wrapper gap, (C) lane exhaustion, or
(D) call site in a no-ring image. No new migrations, no duplex/psynch, no lane-ownership change.

Metrics (metrics.hpp): recordResidualReason() classifies each UDS call at the server.cpp:723
choke point from server-observable per-(thread,process) state into mutually-exclusive buckets --
thread_no_ring_proc_none/has (reason A), thread_has_ring (B/D: eligible op on UDS despite a live
lane, also bumps udsDespiteLaneByCallnum), control_plane, ineligible. Plus server-side lane
proxies: totalRingThreadsRegistered (lanes acquired) + maxRingThreadsPerProcess (computed off the
hot path at snapshot when armed). Gate residual_census_gate_test.cpp (GREEN + RED arms
-DRED_BREAK_DISARMED_NOOP / -DRED_BREAK_AB_SEPARATION) wired into run-ring-shm-validate.sh.

VERDICT (live, matched dyld+dylib+server, same warm workload): all 231 residual eligible-UDS land
in thread_has_ring (NOT reason A: the thread already owns a lane), and uds_despite_lane names
exactly started_suspended (116) + vchroot_path (115). Reason C is 0 (guest lane stats:
exhausted=0, max 3 lanes/process vs cap 64). So the residual is B/D -- two early-init call sites
miss the ring ~once per process, rooted in the PER-IMAGE lane-table split (dserver-ring.c is
compiled into BOTH the main dylib `emulation` and the dyld image `emulation_dyld`, each with its
own g_lanes; started_suspended is VARIANT_DYLD-only; vchroot_path also has a structurally-UDS
mldr.c caller). The proposed D18 "attach-then-send-same-call" is ALREADY the wrapper's behavior
and would not help; the real next step is the per-image lane-handoff (a small ~2/process tail).
Top total-UDS sources are all expected non-ring classes (pthread floor, control-plane handshakes,
blocking waits, pre-attach dyld-image ops) -- D9's "hot != reclaimable" holds. Doc + snapshot
included. Prod restored + md5-verified.
