dup_fd fix confirmed: sys 5.72s->3.90s (-32%), wall 1.73->1.24s (-28%),
dup_fd 13.30%->0.09%. DSO split unchanged (dup_fd was kernel): clang 35%,
dyld 21%, libsystem_kernel 16%, platform/malloc ~9% each.

NEW #1 kernel bucket = mmap/pagefault/pagetable 12.8% (was dup_fd),
driven by per-process VM teardown (do_exit->exit_mmap->zap_pte_range) +
fork pte-copy + dyld library fault-in. Syscall time still blocking-wait
dominated (wait4/recvmsg/poll), off-CPU, not a CPU bucket. No fd@1048575.

VERDICT A: dyld/pagefault/startup is the next lever — dyld 21% userspace
(biggest non-clang bucket, abnormal for a compiler) + the ~12.8% kernel
pagefault/mmap it drives across hundreds of short-lived procs. clang ~35%
is real LLVM we can't chase without PMU/baseline. Next bead perf#22: dyld/
startup-mapping attribution (recon-first). NOT touched: NOFILE cap, ring,
psynch, dyld optimization. No code changes.
