+perf#22a mm-split (guest mldr, 3x 200-file clang -j8 builds):
+exit_mmap    1.488s  88%  2508 calls @593us  (AS teardown - DOMINANT)
+copy_page_range 0.203s 12% 237935 calls @853ns (fork COW PTE-copy - cheap, NOT lever)
+faults 2.69M (minor 2.63M, major 155~0 = warm cache); mmap ~206/proc; vm_mmap ~212/exec
+VERDICT E: process reuse / teardown avoidance
diff --git a/tests/p22a-mm.bt b/tests/p22a-mm.bt
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..a89e020426e94be78d518aa27a0c25bc152a70cc
--- /dev/null
+++ b/tests/p22a-mm.bt
@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+// perf#22a: split guest (mldr) mm/startup kernel cost into fork-copy vs exec-teardown vs fault vs exit.
+// kprobes on the key kernel functions; count + time each.
+kprobe:copy_page_range { @t_forkcopy[tid]=nsecs; }          // fork COW PTE copy (dup_mmap->copy_page_range)
+kretprobe:copy_page_range /@t_forkcopy[tid]/ { @forkcopy_ns=sum(nsecs-@t_forkcopy[tid]); @forkcopy=count(); delete(@t_forkcopy[tid]); }
+kprobe:exit_mmap /comm=="mldr"/ { @t_exitmmap[tid]=nsecs; }  // full AS teardown (exec's old-AS free + process exit)
+kretprobe:exit_mmap /@t_exitmmap[tid]/ { @exitmmap_ns=sum(nsecs-@t_exitmmap[tid]); @exitmmap=count(); delete(@t_exitmmap[tid]); }
+kprobe:__handle_mm_fault /comm=="mldr"/ { @t_fault[tid]=nsecs; }
+kretprobe:__handle_mm_fault /@t_fault[tid]/ { @fault_ns=sum(nsecs-@t_fault[tid]); @fault=count(); delete(@t_fault[tid]); }
+// minor vs major fault
+software:page-faults:1 /comm=="mldr"/ { @minorfault=count(); }
+software:major-faults:1 /comm=="mldr"/ { @majorfault=count(); }
+// mmap syscalls (dylib mapping)
+tracepoint:syscalls:sys_enter_mmap /comm=="mldr"/ { @mmap=count(); }
+tracepoint:syscalls:sys_enter_munmap /comm=="mldr"/ { @munmap=count(); }
+END {
+  clear(@t_forkcopy); clear(@t_exitmmap); clear(@t_fault);
+  printf("\n=== FORK PTE-copy (copy_page_range): count + total_ns ===\n"); print(@forkcopy); print(@forkcopy_ns);
+  printf("=== EXEC/EXIT teardown (exit_mmap): count + total_ns ===\n"); print(@exitmmap); print(@exitmmap_ns);
+  printf("=== page fault handler (__handle_mm_fault): count + total_ns ===\n"); print(@fault); print(@fault_ns);
+  printf("=== minor / major faults ===\n"); print(@minorfault); print(@majorfault);
+  printf("=== mmap / munmap syscalls ===\n"); print(@mmap); print(@munmap);
+}

From 698313d9365866a084e0f387db3c00a19362903f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:08:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf#23a:=20process-reuse=20feasibility=20+=20u?=
 =?UTF-8?q?pper-bound=20=E2=80=94=20verdict=20C=20(dyld/mapping=20reductio?=
 =?UTF-8?q?n)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

RECON + upper-bound, no code. Follows perf#22a (VERDICT E: process churn dominates).
Same 200-file clang -j8 workload, compact-fd mldr f0cd2a82 live, prod dserver 835946f9 untouched.

Findings:
- 401/418 execs (95.9%) are clang = 200 driver + 200 cc1 (2 procs/source; clang-900/LLVM-9).
- Every clang maps the identical ~52-dylib libSystem closure (none needed by a compiler);
  exit_mmap 837 calls/428ms vs fork COW 60ms => teardown ~7.1x fork copy.
- UPPER-BOUND (fewer driver invocations):
    baseline 200 drivers -j8 = 1.15s / 418 execs / exit_mmap 837
    batched  1 driver serial  = 2.58s (SLOWER: loses -j8) / 212 / 425
    chunked  8x25 drivers -j8 = 0.65s (-44%) / 217 / 443
  => driver half of churn removable (~50%, only if parallelism kept), but 200 cc1 irreducible
     (clang -c multi-source still forks one cc1 per source).
- clang-900 has NO server/persistent mode; cc1 is one-TU-per-process => transparent worker
  infeasible/out-of-scope. Zygote attacks only the 12% fork side, not the 88% teardown.

VERDICT C: process reuse infeasible => next lever = dyld/mapping reduction (perf#22a bucket-B):
shrink per-proc mapped set + amortise fault-in/exit_mmap teardown across procs (perf#24 recon).
Not A (no reuse mode), not B-as-runtime (batching is a build-system change), not D (zygote misses
teardown), not E (Darling overhead is dyld/mapping, not LLVM).

Artifacts: p23a-census.bt, p23a-{baseline,batch,chunk}-census.txt, p23a-{batch,chunk}.sh, p23a-dylib-set.txt.
