Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

RECON only, no code. Follows perf#23a verdict C. Same 200-file clang -j8, prod dserver 835946f9
+ mldr f0cd2a82 untouched. Darling dyld honors DYLD_PRINT_{LIBRARIES,SEGMENTS,INITIALIZERS,STATISTICS}.

PREFLIGHT FINDING: launcher env is DPREFIX (default ~/.darling), NOT DARLING_PREFIX — so all prior
DARLING_PREFIX cmds ran against ~/.darling. Same shared binaries (835946f9/f0cd2a82 via /proc/exe),
so perf#23a findings valid, label was wrong. perf#24a uses DPREFIX explicitly; 1 clean launchd.

FINDINGS (driver ~= cc1, both load IDENTICAL 41-dylib set, each loaded 2x):
- libSystem.B is an UMBRELLA that eager-links ~33 /usr/lib/system/libsystem_* subs => every process
  linking libSystem pulls the whole closure. clang direct deps only 4 (libncurses/libz/libSystem/libc++).
- pre-main ~3.7ms: initializers 58% (libSystem.B init ~1.1ms=30%), loading 30%, rebase/bind only 7.6%.
  Only libSystem.B + libc++ run own init; 33 subs run none.
- 40 dylibs/proc x3 VMAs = ~120 dylib VMAs; live clang = 189 total VMAs (64% closure).
- NO dead weight: every dylib faulted (small libsystem_* 100% resident); rules out outcome A.
- exit_mmap (100-file -j8): 437 procs, 210ms, 480us/proc, 187 VMAs/proc => closure = 64% of what
  zap_pte_range walks => direct mechanism behind perf#22a's 88% teardown.

VERDICT B+D, NOT A/C/E: closure is needed-but-repeated => map once & SHARE (shared-cache-like),
NOT prune. NOT A (all faulted, none dead). NOT C (bind 7.6%). NOT E (structural libSystem cost, not LLVM).
NEXT perf#24b (design): (1) shared-cache-like single mapping of /usr/lib/system set to collapse ~99
closure VMAs -> fewer VMAs/faults/teardown (not disk; major faults ~0); (2) libSystem.B init audit (D).

Artifacts: p24a-{clang-full,perdylib-1proc,faulted,ranked,smaps,exittime}.txt.
