DESIGN + upper-bound, no production code. Follows perf#24a verdict B+D. Same 200-file clang -j8,
prod dserver 835946f9 + mldr f0cd2a82 untouched. DPREFIX=~/.darling (NOT DARLING_PREFIX).

UPPER-BOUND (host micro-bench, sizes from real perf#24a closure: 40 dylibs/30MB/9.4MB faulted, x400 procs):
  CURRENT 40x3=120 VMAs vs CACHE 6 regions:
    teardown (munmap) 75->8.8ms (8.5x); load (mmap) 36.5->1.9ms (19x); minor faults UNCHANGED (1.0x).
  VMA-isolation (faulted bytes constant): teardown 6vma=138us .. 120vma=419us .. 240vma=628us
    => ~140us page-zap FLOOR + per-VMA component; native 419us@120 matches perf#24a measured 480us/proc.
  Build-wide (x400): exit_mmap 480->162us/proc = ~127ms saved (66%, the perf#22a 88% teardown bucket);
    load ~37ms; minor faults ~0 saved (same bytes fault regardless of packing). ~164ms serial-equiv.
  => GO on mapping side (well above noise). Win is VMA create+teardown+load, NOT fault-in.

DESIGN ACCEPT (minimal): Darling system-closure cache = one packed image for libSystem.B + libsystem_*;
  TEXT/LINKEDIT MAP_SHARED RO, DATA MAP_PRIVATE/COW; dyld maps+registers each as a logical dylib
  (Mach-O identity preserved). Constraints: image list/dladdr/dlsym, init order, ASLR/rebase,
  writable DATA COW, fork/exec survival, path identity. dyld changes in src/external/dyld.

INIT AUDIT (Track 2): 434 initializers, 430 are clang's own LLVM ctors (not addressable); libSystem.B
  init ~0.9-1.2ms (2 funcs) = the addressable init. Source (libsystem/init.c:230-267) sub-inits in order:
  libkernel->libplatform->pthread->libc->malloc->keymgr->dyld->pthread_late->libdispatch->libxpc.
  Lazy candidates: libxpc, keymgr (unproven). Shared mapping does NOT remove this ~1ms init (orthogonal).

RECOMMENDATION C (both, ordered): perf#24c shared-cache prototype FIRST (larger, better-understood,
  bounded correctness), THEN perf#24d libSystem.B init laziness only if still meaningful. Not B-first
  (init smaller/riskier), not STOP (upper-bound cleared bar). NOT touched: prune/reuse/vfork/ring/LLVM/bind.

Artifacts: p24b-upperbound.c, p24b-vmacost.c, p24b-upperbound-results.txt.
