 =?UTF-8?q?ilder)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

FEASIBILITY GATE, no cache built, no dyld patched. Rescoped from perf#24c per user (minimal-prototype
framing understated the work). Mach-O audit of libSystem.B + 25 libsystem_*/closure dylibs from install
tree (inode-verified == guest mappings). prod dserver 835946f9 + mldr f0cd2a82 untouched.

MECHANISM: dyld3 mapImage = per dylib vm_allocate + 3x mmap(MAP_FIXED|MAP_PRIVATE) = 3 VMAs/dylib
(distinct perms, kernel won't coalesce; diff files never coalesce; DATA bss gap blocks whole-file mmap).
120 dylib VMAs. Collapse requires packed cache file (concat same-perm segments -> 1 mmap/plane) + reader.

AUDIT (all 26 dylibs): __TEXT relocs=0 (PIC, no text rewriting), __DATA_CONST=0 (no laterReadOnly
re-mprotect re-split, Loading.cpp:991 never fires), all fixups=rebase/bind in DATA, unwind in __TEXT (RO
shareable). TEXT/DATA linear (vmaddr==fileoff); LINKEDIT offset by DATA bss gap but independently mappable.
LINKEDIT consumers (LC_DYLD_INFO_ONLY/SYMTAB/DYSYMTAB/FUNCTION_STARTS/DATA_IN_CODE) = absolute file offsets
=> builder must rewrite by linkedit delta (header-only, NO code bytes).

ANSWER: YES packable into TEXT/DATA/LINKEDIT planes without text rewriting. Builder fixups = header-only
offset rewrites (LC_SEGMENT_64.fileoff + LINKEDIT-consumer offsets); vmaddr/vmsize UNCHANGED => dladdr/dlsym/
rebase/bind identical => identity preserved. TEXT+LINKEDIT MAP_SHARED RO, DATA MAP_PRIVATE/COW.

TOY VALIDATOR (static): p24c0-validate.sh 26/26 dylibs 52/52 checks pass; p24c0-pack.py 2-dylib transform
proves valid plane offsets + vmaddr/vmsize preserved (identity/dlsym/dladdr), init order graph-driven,
DATA COW. 120 -> 3 planes. Live reader NOT built (that's perf#24c1/c2, would pre-empt decision).

DECISION A: full packed-cache builder FEASIBLE -> fund perf#24c1 (builder: 3 planes + image table + header
fixups) + perf#24c2 (flag-gated dyld reader mapping 3 planes, mirror inDyldCache fast path Loading.cpp:303,
A/B VMA/load/teardown). Not B (no text rewriting; init laziness stays separate perf#24d). Not C (large
layout-preserving reduction). Projected: 120->~3-6 VMAs, exit_mmap ~480->162us/proc (~127ms build-wide).

Artifacts: p24c0-validate.sh/.txt, p24c0-pack.py/.txt.
