HARD GATE before c1/c2, no code. Answers the negotiable invariant: dyld resolves EVERY segment via
getSlide() = loadedAddress - __TEXT.vmaddr (single TEXT-derived slide), used by fixups (Loading.cpp:797),
dladdr/findSectionContent (MachOLoaded.cpp:691), intersectsRange (:701). forEachCacheSegment per-segment
cacheOffset (Closure.cpp:426) EXISTS but is used only for mapping/logging, NOT by runtime resolvers => no
translation table in the hot path.

CONSEQUENCE: every segment must sit at loadedAddress + (seg.vmaddr - TEXT.vmaddr). This INVALIDATES the
perf#24c0 "3 independent planes, vmaddr unchanged" sketch (DATA/LINK would compute into the TEXT plane).

CORRECT MODEL (how macOS shared cache does it, CacheBuilder.cpp): per-permission CONTIGUOUS regions
(RX=all TEXT, RW=all DATA, RO=all LINKEDIT) with each image's segment VMADDRS REWRITTEN to region-relative
positions so a single slide reproduces every segment addr; VMA collapse from same-perm segments contiguous
in one region. Survives vmaddr rewrite: rebase/bind use SEG_INDEX+offset (MachOAnalyzer.cpp:1234); LINKEDIT
consumers = file offsets (rewrite by delta). Builder rewrites LC_SEGMENT_64.{vmaddr,fileoff}+LINKEDIT offsets;
code bytes untouched.

VERDICT: proceed with CORRECTED region model (not 3 arbitrary planes). inDyldCache() path does NOT already
support arbitrary multi-mapping-per-image => per user rule, 2-dylib LIVE reader smoke REQUIRED before full
closure (static insufficient; single-slide x region layout must be executed). c1/c2 tasks updated.
