From 244ab89d7c26814f50405ad1ef507567ee10809b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 08:48:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#24c2a: DCC1 reader RED LINE + DCC2 rescope + fixup/bind
 audit

Stopped the DCC1 flag-gated live-reader at a RED LINE and rescoped to DCC2
(region-packed cache + cache-native precomputed fixup table + dyld DCC path
that skips normal Mach-O fixups). No dyld code written, nothing deployed.

Findings:
- Builder bug found+fixed: c1 rewrote seg vmaddrs only in the dcc_seg table,
  not in the packed mach-o header (LC_SEGMENT_64.vmaddr) that dyld actually
  reads via getSlide()/preferredLoadAddress(). A reader-proxy harness that
  reads the header like dyld FAILED table-only and PASSES after adding a
  header-rewrite pass to the builder.
- Red line: Darling takes the dyld3 closure path at launch (verified live via
  DYLD_PRINT_SEGMENTS), but applyFixupsToImage/WrappedMachO::forEachFixup
  assume each image is one contiguous [TEXT|DATA|LINKEDIT] vmaddr span
  (measured DATA-TEXT delta == DATA fileoff for every dylib). The region model
  scatters segments, so normal fixups resolve wrong. macOS dodges this by
  pre-applying fixups + inDyldCache skip (Loading.cpp:331).
- Fixup/bind audit (full 40-dylib closure): 100% opcode encoding, zero chained
  fixups; 23407 rebases + 1395 binds; every ord bind targets an in-closure
  dylib (build-time resolvable); only 5 flat + 154 self special-ordinal binds.
  2-dylib smoke pair chosen = {libsystem_blocks, libunwind} (self-contained).

Artifacts: tests/PERF24C2A-READER-REDLINE-DCC2-AUDIT.md, tools/closure-cache/
audit/ (slide-harness.c, fixup-audit.c + audit-full.txt, deltas.c, check_hdr.c).
prod dserver 835946f9 + mldr f0cd2a82 + dyld 10af572e untouched. LOCAL only.
