From 927f262c048b9c543c66466596cf12b3a35dd455 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 09:43:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#24c2c: live dyld DCC2 reader implemented; smoke blocked
 on dyld/dylib version skew

Implemented a flag-gated live DCC2 reader in the dyld3 launch path (preserved
here under tools/closure-cache/dyld-reader-wip/ since the dyld submodule edits
are uncommitted): DCC2Reader.{h,cpp} maps the 3 packed regions into one arena
(RX+RO MAP_SHARED, RW MAP_PRIVATE/COW) preserving relative spacing, validates
magic/version + per-image staleness, and applies the cache-native fixup table
(rebase / bind_internal / bind_extern via findExportedSymbol, no silent NULL).
mapAndFixupAllImages takes over DCC2 images and applies the table; the invariant
that a DCC2 image must never enter the normal Mach-O fixup engine is enforced
with a hard halt. Feature-gated by DARLING_DYLD_DCC2=1 + DARLING_DYLD_DCC2_PATH;
absent = exact old behavior. dyld built clean.

Live 2-dylib smoke is BLOCKED by a pre-existing version skew, NOT by the DCC2
code. Clean A/B bisect: the deployed baseline dyld (10af572e) boots; a pristine
current-tree dyld with ZERO DCC2 edits (d4ca8c3f, dyld submodule HEAD a9c2e29
dated 2026-06-09) does NOT boot (silent shellspawn hang); my DCC2 dyld fails
identically. Root cause: the deployed closure dylibs are dated 2026-06-15 (newer
than the checked-out dyld submodule), so rebuilding only dyld from the current
tree is incompatible with the deployed dylib closure. Resolution (before retry):
rebuild+redeploy the closure dylibs from the current tree and verify a plain
d4ca8c3f boots flag-off first, or build dyld from the source that produced the
deployed baseline. The DCC2 mechanism itself is already proven correct offline
(perf#24c2b builder + standalone applier: 7 acceptance checks + 4 RED arms).

Environment left healthy (baseline dyld restored and booting). prod dserver
835946f9 + mldr f0cd2a82 untouched. LOCAL only.
