From a988049bf2870de1651b6ac2361f9fea504f2bd4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 10:14:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#24c2c-pre: DCC2 reader exonerated; boot blocker is
 build/toolchain mismatch
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root-caused the c2c live-smoke blocker with a corrected clean-teardown protocol
(the confound was a leftover orphaned mldr /sbin/launchd from a wedged prior
boot that silently blocks shellspawn; the teardown must kill it by PID).

Clean boot matrix:
- prod-bak 79b22273 (pre-built matched backup): BOOTS reliably.
- built 63f667c (submodule pointer): does NOT boot.
- built a9c2e29 (branch HEAD, zero DCC2 edits): does NOT boot.
- built a9c2e29 + DCC2 reader: does NOT boot, identically.

Conclusions: (1) the DCC2 reader is exonerated — a clean-tree dyld with none of
my edits fails identically; (2) no dyld built from this tree/toolchain boots at
any commit, while only the pre-built matched binary does. So the blocker is a
build-environment/toolchain mismatch, not a source-commit choice. The preferred
path (align dyld source + rebuild only dyld) is therefore not viable; the only
remaining route to the live smoke is the fallback: rebuild+redeploy the whole
closure (dyld + dylibs + mldr, one build) in a disposable prefix, prove a plain
flag-OFF boot there first, then enable DCC2.

DCC2 mechanism already proven correct offline (perf#24c2b). Environment left
healthy on working baseline 79b22273 (both prefix copies); prod mldr f0cd2a82
intact. LOCAL only.
---
