Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf#24c2d:=20DCC2=20builder=20=E2=80=94=20rewr?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ite=20section=20addrs,=20not=20just=20segment=20vmaddrs?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The DCC2 builder rewrote each LC_SEGMENT_64.vmaddr to region-relative
absolute (so seg.vmaddr + fSlide == mapped region addr under the single-slide
model), but left the per-section section_64.addr fields at their ORIGINAL
vmaddrs. dyld's parseLoadCmds (ImageLoaderMachO.cpp:804) dereferences
(sect->addr + fSlide) for specific sections such as __objc_imageinfo; with a
stale section addr that lands outside the mapped region and reads garbage.

Live full-40-dylib DCC2 boot: libdispatch (first closure dylib carrying an
__objc_imageinfo section) hit a spurious "Objective-C garbage collection is
not supported" throw. The 2-dylib smoke {libsystem_blocks,libunwind} passed
only because neither carries such a section.

Fix: in the packed-header rewrite pass, for every LC_SEGMENT_64 apply the same
(new_vmaddr - old_vmaddr) delta to each contained section_64.addr, then set the
segment vmaddr. Cache validates identically (fixup counts unchanged; section
addrs are read by parseLoadCmds, not by the fixup engine). Live effect: all
40 images now substitute (was 15 before the throw), 24,802 fixups apply once
for the whole cache, and load-time validation passes for the full closure.

Remaining (separate edge): early launchd still takes a SIGSEGV after dyld
handoff / early initializers — a runtime DATA-fixup correctness edge, not a
load-time failure.
