From 9150a46a0dde1b26a524f610a6eecbdb45af8df3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 15:53:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf#24c2d:=20DCC2=20builder=20=E2=80=94=20cove?=
 =?UTF-8?q?r=20lazy/weak=20binds=20+=20rebase=20values=20+=20lazy-tolerant?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20externs?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three further full-closure correctness fixes found by live 40-dylib DCC2 boot
(the 2-dylib smoke could not surface any of them — leaf dylibs lack the load
commands / sections involved):

1. Walk LAZY and WEAK bind streams, not just the regular bind stream. DCC2
   skips the normal fixup engine entirely, so every pointer slot must be fixed
   at build time — including __la_symbol_ptr (lazy). Missing them left those
   slots holding raw file bytes (stale __stub_helper vmaddr) => deref lands on
   Mach-O header/section-table bytes; observed SIGSEGV fault address == the
   ASCII bytes "__text" (a section_64.sectname). Fixups 24,802 -> 27,082.

2. Translate the stored REBASE pointer VALUES. A rebase slot holds an original
   same-image vmaddr; the reader does *loc += slide (slide=arena). After
   region-repacking the target lives at region_relative_vmaddr+arena, so each
   stored value must be translated original -> region-relative (by the
   containing source segment's delta) before the slide is added. Without this,
   every non-zero-repacked image (all but image 0) rebased to garbage.

3. Lazy binds whose symbol is genuinely absent (Darling stub gap, e.g.
   libcorecrypto's _ccchacha20 — 11 in this closure) must NOT hard-fail. Normal
   dyld resolves lazy binds on first call; an unused missing symbol never
   faults. Eager DCC2 resolution turned that into a whole-process abort
   (abort_with_payload "applyAllFixupsOnce failed"). New fixup kind
   DCC_FIX_BIND_EXTERN_LAZY: reader resolves if possible, else writes a sentinel
   (0), preserving lazy resolve/trap-on-first-call semantics. Format bumped with
   the new kind; applier validator updated to accept it.

Live effect: all 40 images substitute, 27,082 fixups apply once for the whole
cache, the extern abort and the earlier libdispatch ObjC-GC throw are gone.
Remaining (documented, next lead): early launchd still SIGSEGVs at a "__text"
(section-name) address — one more wrongly-translated or uncovered DATA pointer.
