 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20full=20closure=20/usr/bin/true=20exit=200,=20no=20"?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=5F=5Ftext"=20crash?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The RIP-relative rewrite fixes the DCC2 crash LIVE. Same 40-dylib closure that
SIGSEGV'd on "__text" under unrewritten DCC2 (task #97) now runs /usr/bin/true
to exit 0 with 38 images substituted from the DCC5 cache and 27082 fixups
applied once.

Sequence (all pass): (1) DCC5 OFF rebuilt dyld boots clean, zero DCC2 lines;
(2) DCC5 ON 2-dylib smoke {libsystem_blocks,libunwind} — cache maps, images
substituted, 83 fixups once, rewritten stubs work; (3) DCC5 ON full closure —
/usr/bin/true exit 0, no __text SIGSEGV, no fixup fallback, only the 11 expected
lazy stub-gap externs (sentinel).

Build: xnu@a0328833 for dyld+libsystem_kernel, then restored perf/shmem-ring-guest;
deployed built dyld (1469bbad) to both closure copies. Key deploy fix: the guest
resolves /usr/lib to the libexec/darling tree, so the cache must be built with
install_root=<prefix>/libexec/darling or the reader's inode staleness check
hard-fails. Prod dyld/mldr/dserver restored byte-identical afterward (doctor ALL
GREEN). Empirical per-process VMA count deferred to the A/B bead (flag reaches
only the transient leaf guest command here).
