so the remaining crash is NOT a missed rewrite. Corrected task #101: the smoke
exit-0 was a false pass (launcher rc, not guest-child rc); /usr/bin/true and
clang both SIGSEGV (139) in libSystem.B init. 6 fault-PC capture attempts failed
because Darling spawns the guest in a separate PID namespace and translates the
guest SIGSEGV to a Mach exception before any host-observable fault (crashcap-sigexc
too early; strace/gdb wrong tree or clean exit). Remaining path: container-side
gdbserver or a dserver exception-state dump. Prod restored byte-identical (doctor
