MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DCC6 shared-cache prototype: functionally proven + kernel-measured. Rolls up
the whole perf#24 arc (#79-#109).

- DCC6 = a launch-churn optimization, NOT a compiler-CPU optimization.
- Kernel proof: unmap_vmas -78.3%, zap_pte_range -66.3%, exit_mmap CPU -17.7%.
- Tiny launch-heavy workloads benefit (200-file -17% wall); CPU-bound 500-file
  build does not move (OFF==ON, teardown saving ~1.4% of a compile-bound build).
- Status: prototype / flag-gated / NOT default-on; productization = separate
  hardening.
- Two honest continuation branches documented (A: libSystem init laziness for
  launch-heavy; B: compiler CPU attribution for build-bound — or stop).

No new fix. Decision record only.
